(82965, 'sp-cloudkill', '5e', 2, 'Text', 'When a creature enters the spell\'s area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, that creature must make a Constitution saving throw. The creature takes 5d8 poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. Creatures are affected even if they hold their breath or don\'t need to breathe.'),
(82964, 'sp-cloudkill', '5e', 1, 'Text', 'You create a 20-foot-radius sphere of poisonous, yellow-green fog centered on a point you choose within range. The fog spreads around corners. It lasts for the duration or until strong wind disperses the fog, ending the spell. Its area is heavily obscured.'),
